REDIS-INIT

About:
  Init script for run multi redis nodes with dedicated configs.

Setup:
  If you use debian, simple build and install package. Otherwise copy and rename init
  in compliance with your distribution.
  Configure variables $CONFIG_DIR, $DAEMON according to your setup.
  Put your config_name.conf into $CONFIG_DIR.

Usage:
  sudo /etc/init.d/redis-init start foo
  sudo /etc/init.d/redis-init stop foo
  sudo /etc/init.d/redis-init stop all
  sudo /etc/init.d/redis-init status all
